le chance of influencing national policy debates. The phenomenon of “members without advocates” thus has enormous implications for democratic participation in Japan.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Civics & Citizenship.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150362606540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503626065423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503626065/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles